	<key>readme</key>
	<string>When In… — keyword `when`, then a subcommand:

  when in &lt;place&gt;   — current time in a city or country (fuzzy)
  when tz &lt;zone&gt;    — time for a tz code (PST) or IANA name (Europe/Berlin)
  when is &lt;country&gt; — public holidays (coming soon)

`when &lt;place&gt;` with no subcommand also does a city lookup. Press Enter to copy a chat-ready line like "2:32 PM Fri in Rome (CEST, UTC+2)".

Set the clock format (12h/24h) in this workflow's configuration.</string>
